From Henry's review: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-networkd/+/73149

We have feedback from Johnathan Mantey,

My suggestion is to add '-o/--option' and then apply mandatory string option names, such as:
-o get-vid, -o get-aen, -o set-aen [1|0], etc....

Please change as per this suggestion

This has been bugging me....
Why doesn't this command have an argument?
It should be possible to assert (i.e. =1) and deassert (i.e. =0) bits 0..2.
This command should accept values between 0 and 7
Hi Johnathan, addressed review comments. Kindly check
Confirm incoming mask byte is between 0...7, and pass to AEN_ENABLE command
Add input for assigning values between 0...7

We'll need to be careful in any conflicts with the kernel's own usage of the NCSI interface here.

Mainly: how are you planning to receive the actual AENs that result from the enable?

Hi Jeremy,
This review is to provide an option to enable AEN using ncsi-netlink.
I will create another review to handle receiving the actual AENs.

The kernel doesn't have a facility to forward incoming AENs to userspace though. You may be able to send the Enable command, but you'll have no facility to receive the subsequent AENs.

[The kernel has no way to determine whether an incoming AEN is destined for the kernel management stack, or the userspace process. Also, note that the kernel has probably already enabled AENs for the links that it is interested in]

If you have kernel changes in mind here, might be good to check those out first.
Hi Jeremy, thank you for the suggestion. Will look into it.
